[style name="res://Dialogue/Styles/CozyPersonaVN.tres"]
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
The morning sun shines over the quiet neighborhood.
A sedan is parked neatly outside the Ilagan house.
The street is calm. A few neighbors sweep their front yards while children walk toward school.
The front gate slowly opens.
Ethan walks toward the house carrying a small paper bag from a local bakery.
He pauses for a moment before ringing the doorbell.
DING DONG.
[signal arg="sfx:doorbell"]
A few seconds pass.
The door opens.
Ricardo stands at the doorway.
His expression immediately softens.
Ethan. Maaga ka ah.
Chuckling.
May dala po akong pandesal.
Fresh pa.
Ricardo smiles.
Aba... Sakto.
Kape na lang kulang.
Pasok ka na, hijo.
Ethan steps inside.
The house feels unusually quiet.
The television is off.
No music plays.
The silence feels heavier than usual.
Ethan notices Jennifer arranging a few things on a nearby shelf.
Ethan notices Jennifer standing near the living room.
She's looking down at her phone.
Her thumb scrolls absentmindedly through social media.
Good morning po, Tita.
Jennifer doesn't respond immediately.
Still focused on her screen.
A beat passes.
She suddenly looks up.
Ay...
Good morning, Ethan.
Pasensya na.
Ethan smiles politely.
Okay lang po.
He hands her the paper bag.
May pandesal po.
Naku.
Hindi na sana nag-abala.
Okay lang po.
Napadaan lang.
Jennifer smiles politely.
But her eyes betray her exhaustion.
She hasn't been sleeping well.
Ethan notices.
He doesn't mention it.
Instead...
Nasaan po si Maya?
Jennifer pauses.
She glances toward the hallway.
Nasa kwarto pa nya..
Ethan nods.
The answer is enough.
Ricardo walks toward the kitchen.
Kape muna tayo.
Baka magising din 'yon si Maya.
The aroma of freshly brewed coffee fills the room.
The paper bag of pandesal sits in the middle of the table.
Jennifer begins serving everyone.
The atmosphere is noticeably lighter than it has been in days.
Buti napadaan ka, Ethan.
Hindi ka na masyadong nakakabisita rito.
Medyo naging busy lang po.
Thesis.
Requirements.
Alam n'yo naman.
Ricardo nods absentmindedly.
His phone vibrates beside his coffee.
[signal arg="sfx:phone_notif"]
[signal arg="emotion_persist:nervous:2"]
He glances at the screen.
A customer asking for an update on a repair.
Without thinking...
He begins typing a reply.
Raising an eyebrow.
Hon...
Mamaya na 'yan.
Kumakain tayo.
Ricardo looks up.
As if only now realizing what he was doing.
Ah. Sorry.
He locks his phone and sets it beside his plate.
Smiles.
Okay lang po, Tito.
Work is work.
Chuckles sheepishly.
Sensya na, minsan...nadadala lang talaga.
Normal lang 'yan.
Last stretch na.
Konting tiis na lang.
Ethan nods.
Jennifer smiles proudly.
She glances toward Maya's empty seat.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:lost:2"]
Gano'n din si Maya.
Halos hindi na nga lumalabas ng kwarto kakaaral.
Kung minsan kailangan ko pang pilitin magpahinga.
Ricardo smiles.
Mana sa sipag.
Jennifer chuckles.
Kaya nga kahit nahihirapan...
Alam kong kakayanin niya.
Hindi naman basta sumusuko ang anak namin.
Ethan smiles politely.
He hesitates.
Unsure whether to say anything.
Then...
Actually po... Okay na ba siya?
The room grows quieter.
Jennifer looks at him. Confused.
Anong ibig mong sabihin?
Ethan blinks.
He immediately realizes something is off.
Ah...
Akala ko po... Nasabi na niya.
Jennifer slowly lowers her spoon.
Nasabi ang alin?
Ethan looks between Jennifer and Ricardo.
Then toward the hallway.
His expression changes.
He wasn't supposed to be the one saying it.
He remembers the message Maya sent him weeks ago, venting about the failed requirement.
He assumed that if she told him, she'd told them too.
He never considered that texting him had been the safer version of the truth.
...
About po doon sa...major requirement niya.
Silence.
Ricardo frowns.
Anong requirement?
Ethan swallows.
His voice becomes quieter.
Yung... Hindi niya po naipasa.
The room falls completely silent.
Jennifer stares at him.
As if she misheard.
...
Ano?
Ethan quickly shakes his head.
Tita... Akala ko talaga alam n'yo na.
I'm sorry.
Jennifer slowly stands.
Her eyes remain fixed on Ethan.
Hindi niya sinabi sa'min.
Ricardo's expression hardens.
He looks toward the hallway leading to Maya's room.
A mixture of confusion...
And disappointment.
Kailan pa nangyari 'to?
Ethan rubs the back of his neck.
Clearly uncomfortable.
Matagal na po.
I... I thought napag-usapan niyo na.
Nobody responds.
The silence becomes unbearable.
Jennifer slowly exhales.
Trying to process everything.
So...
Habang sinasabi niyang okay lang siya... Habang sinasabi niyang kaya niya...
Hindi pala totoo.
Ricardo doesn't answer.
His jaw tightens.
For the first time...
Neither parent knows what to believe anymore.
Ethan looks toward Maya's closed bedroom door.
Guilt washes over him.
He never intended to expose her.
He simply assumed...
Her parents already knew.
Instead...
He had revealed the truth himself.
And in doing so...
The trust inside the Ilagan household quietly began to crumble.
The dining table remains untouched.
The cups of coffee have gone cold.
Ricardo sits at the head of the table.
Jennifer quietly folds a dish towel in her hands, more out of nervousness than necessity.
Ethan sits across from them.
No one says a word.
Ricardo breaks the silence.
Hindi puwedeng ganito na lang, Jen.
Jennifer looks up and sighs.
Alam ko pero-.
Pause.
-pero hindi ko alam kung paano magsisimula.
Ricardo nods in agreement.
Ethan looks toward the hallway.
Maybe...
Hindi niyo kailangang alam agad ang tamang sasabihin.
Baka...
kailangan lang muna niyang maramdaman na gusto niyo siyang pakinggan.
Jennifer slowly lowers her eyes.
She quietly nods.
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/mayas_room.png" fade="0.7"]
A soft knock is heard.
Anak...
Pwede ba tayong mag-usap?
Maya looks up from her phone and towards the door.
She takes a deep breath.
[signal arg="sfx:breath_shaky"]
"..."
Her eyes are tired.
She doesn't answer immediately.
Another knock.
Gentler this time.
join Maya (neutral) left [animation="Instant In"]
Maya: ...
Please.
Maya closes her eyes.
She lets out a slow breath.
Then quietly stands.
She unlocks the door.
The door slowly opens.
Ricardo stands in front.
Jennifer is beside him.
Both wear expressions of concern.
Ethan remains a few steps behind in the hallway.
Giving the family space.
For a brief moment...
No one speaks.
Pwede ba tayong mag-usap?
Maya avoids eye contact.
She gives a small shrug.
Kung tungkol na naman sa grades...
Alam ko na sasabihin n'yo.
Hindi.
Gusto lang naming marinig ka.
update Maya (glad)
Maya lets out a quiet, humorless laugh.
Talaga?
Pause.
Ngayon lang?
Jennifer looks down.
She says nothing.
Labas muna tayo.
Usap lang.
Walang sigawan.
Maya studies both of her parents.
Trying to decide if she believes them.
After a long moment...
She quietly nods.
leave Maya [animation="Instant Out"]
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
The living room feels unusually quiet.
Ricardo sits in the single armchair.
Jennifer sits at one end of the sofa.
Maya chooses the opposite end.
Leaving as much distance as possible between them.
Silence.
The ticking of the wall clock becomes almost unbearable.
Ricardo finally speaks.
Anak...
Hindi namin gustong umabot tayo sa ganito.
Maya keeps her eyes fixed on the floor.
Okay lang.
Nangyari na.
Hindi.
Hindi okay.
Pause.
Gusto naming maintindihan...
Bakit umabot dito.
Maya leans back against the sofa.
Crossing her arms.
Almost instinctively.
Building a wall between herself and her parents.
Wala namang complicated.
Bumagsak ako.
Nagalit kayo.
Tapos.
join Maya (neutral) left [animation="Instant In"]
Maya: ...
Hindi lang 'yon.
Matagal na naming napapansin na may tinatago ka.
Maya immediately responds.
Wala.
Anak...
Sabi ngang wala.
Jennifer falls silent.
Ricardo exchanges a quick glance with her.
He notices Maya's defensive tone.
But remains calm.
Hindi namin kalaban, anak.
update Maya (smile)
Maya gives a faint, sarcastic smile.
Hindi ba?
Kasi parang buong semester...
Pakiramdam ko lagi akong nasa hearing.
Laging may kailangang ipaliwanag.
Laging may kulang.
Ricardo exhales.
Still keeping his composure.
Kaya nga gusto naming marinig 'yung side mo.
Maya shakes her head.
Ano pa bang point?
Kahit anong sabihin ko...
May mali pa rin naman.
A heavy silence settles over the room.
join Jennifer (neutral) right [animation="Instant In"]
Jennifer's patience begins to wear thin.
Ricardo notices.
He quietly raises a hand.
A silent plea for her to stay calm.
Maya looks away.
Avoiding both of their eyes.
The distance between them grows heavier with every passing second.
The silence stretches.
Heavy.
Uncomfortable.
Jennifer finally exhales.
Her patience begins to crack.
Maya: ...
Hanggang kailan mo ba sasabihing "wala"?
Hanggang kailan mo itatago lahat sa'min?
Wala naman kasi talagang dapat pag-usapan.
Talaga?
So okay lang na nalaman pa namin sa ibang tao?
Hindi man lang sa sarili naming anak?
Hindi ko sinabi kasi alam ko namang ganito rin mangyayari.
Ganito?
Anong "ganito"?
Concerned kami sa'yo!
Concerned?
O disappointed?
Jennifer's expression hardens.
Maya: .
Inaayos ka namin.
Hindi.
Kinokontrol n'yo ako.
Ricardo immediately steps in.
Tama na.
[signal arg="grain:surge"]
[signal arg="emotion_persist:angry:2"]
Huwag na nating taasan ang boses.
update Maya (glad)
Maya lets out a bitter laugh.
Hindi pa nga ako sumisigaw, Pa.
Pause.
Pero parang bawal na rin pala magsalita.
Walang nagsasabing bawal.
Pero sana...
Panagutan mo rin ang mga ginagawa mo.
Maya slowly stands.
Her arms remain crossed.
Her breathing becomes heavier.
Pinapanagutan ko naman.
Araw-araw.
Hindi n'yo lang nakikita.
Hindi namin nakikita?
Maya: ...
Kami ang nagpapaaral sa'yo.
Kami ang gumagawa ng paraan para makapagtapos ka.
Tapos sasabihin mong hindi namin nakikita?
Maya clenches her jaw.
She stays silent.
Jennifer mistakes the silence for defiance.
Tingnan mo si Ethan.
Maya's eyes immediately shift.
Jennifer continues.
Unable to stop herself.
Pareho kayong Engineering.
May problema rin sila sa bahay.
Pero tumutulong pa rin siya sa mama niya.
Tumutulong pa sa talyer.
Hindi nagtatago.
Hindi nagsisinungaling.
At hindi sumusuko.
Ricardo glances at Jennifer.
He knows exactly where this is going.
Jen...
Jennifer doesn't stop.
Kung nagagawa niya...
Bakit ikaw hindi?
The words hang in the room.
Maya freezes.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:nervous:2"]
Her hands slowly unclench.
She stares at her parents.
Not angry.
Not crying.
Just...
Empty.
A thousand thoughts race through her mind.
Every comparison.
Every expectation.
Every moment she convinced herself to stay quiet.
Her breathing becomes shaky.
She laughs once.
A broken, exhausted laugh.
Alam n'yo ba...
Ilang beses ko nang narinig 'yan?
Pause.
"Tingnan mo si Ethan."
"Bakit hindi mo gayahin si Ethan?"
"Ang sipag ni Ethan."
"Ang galing ni Ethan."
Her voice begins to shake.
Hindi niyo ba naisip...
Na baka...
Nakakapagod na rin marinig?
Long silence.
Maya wipes at her eyes.
Frustrated that the tears won't stop.
[signal arg="drain:on"]
[signal arg="emotion_persist:sad:2"]
Hindi ko naman siya kinaiinggitan.
Best friend ko siya.
Masaya ako para sa kanya.
Pero...
Sa tuwing ikinukumpara n'yo ako...
Pakiramdam ko...
Hindi ako magiging sapat.
Kahit anong gawin ko.
Her breathing becomes uneven.
[signal arg="grain:surge"]
Years of emotions begin pouring out.
Alam n'yo ba kung gaano kahirap pumasok araw-araw...
Sa kursong...
Hindi ko na alam kung gusto ko pa?
Kung gaano kahirap gumising...
Na ang una mong iniisip...
"Huwag lang akong magkamali."
"Huwag lang akong madisappoint sila."
Pause.
Kasi alam kong...
Kapag sinabi ko ang totoo...
Madidisappoint ko kayo.
Her voice finally breaks.
Kaya nanahimik na lang ako.
Kaya tinago ko lahat.
Kaya nagpanggap akong okay.
Hindi dahil gusto ko kayong lokohin...
Kundi dahil...
Takot na takot akong hindi n'yo na ako tanggapin.
The room falls silent.
Nobody speaks.
Maya stands in the middle of the living room.
Breathing heavily.
Her tears continue to fall.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:sad:2"]
For the first time...
Everything she has buried for years...
Has finally been spoken aloud.
But instead of relief...
The silence that follows feels colder than ever.
The room remains completely still.
Maya's words linger in the air.
No one speaks.
Her breathing is uneven.
She waits.
Hoping...
For someone to finally understand.
Instead...
Jennifer slowly stands.
Her expression is unreadable.
When she speaks...
Her voice is calm.
Too calm.
Tapos?
Pause.
'Yan na ba?
Maya looks at her. Confused.
'Yan na lang ba ang sasabihin mo pagkatapos ng lahat?
Na pagod ka?
Na ayaw mo na?
Maya immediately shakes her head.
Hindi ko sinabing ayaw ko-
Pero 'yon ang naririnig ko.
Ricardo quietly lowers his gaze.
Jennifer continues.
Her composure beginning to crack.
Maya: ...
Hindi biro ang ginawa naming sakripisyo.
Ilang taon kaming nag-ipon.
Nagtrabaho.
Nagtipid.
Para lang mapag-aral ka.
Tapos ngayon...
Sasabihin mong hindi mo pala gusto?
update Maya (teary)
Maya's eyes well with tears.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:sad:2"]
Ma...
Sinubukan ko.
Promise.
Araw-araw kong sinubukan.
Pero hindi sapat ang "sinubukan."
Kailangan mong tapusin.
Maya falls silent.
Jennifer takes another step forward.
Akala ko nahihirapan ka lang.
Hindi ko akalaing...
Susuko ka.
Maya's voice trembles.
Hindi ako sumusuko...
Pagod lang talaga ako.
Lahat napapagod.
Hindi lang ikaw.
Ricardo finally speaks.
His voice is lower.
Colder than before.
Anak...
Hindi namin puwedeng gawing dahilan ang pagod.
Maraming tao ang nahihirapan.
Pero tinatapos pa rin nila.
Maya slowly looks at him.
The disappointment in his eyes hurts more than anger ever could.
Pa...
Akala ko mas matatag ka.
The words hit Maya hard.
Jennifer stands and walks toward Maya's room.
A moment later, she returns holding the ipad.
The same account she found weeks ago, now impossible to unsee.
She opens it, scanning through a few sketches.
Drafts.
Portraits.
Landscapes.
Detailed illustrations.
She closes it with a quiet thud.
Ito ba?
Ito ang pinagkakaabalahan mo?
Habang unti-unti kang bumabagsak?
Maya instinctively reaches for it.
Ma...
Please.
Ito ba ang dahilan kung bakit nawawala ka sa focus?
Kung bakit hindi mo na kayang panindigan ang kurso mo?
Maya shakes her head repeatedly.
Hindi.
Hindi n'yo naiintindihan-
Hindi, Maya.
Ikaw ang hindi nakakaintindi.
Ang drawing...
Hobby lang 'yan.
Hindi 'yan ang bubuhay sa'yo.
Hindi 'yan ang magbabayad ng bills.
Hindi 'yan ang magbibigay sa'yo ng maayos na kinabukasan.
Maya stands frozen.
Jennifer's words cut deeper with every sentence.
Kung gusto mong ayusin ang buhay mo...
Unahin mo ang responsibilidad mo.
Hindi 'yang mga drawing na 'yan.
She tucks the ipad under her arm.
Maya's breathing becomes shaky.
She reaches into her hoodie pocket.
Instinctively gripping her phone.
Jennifer notices.
Pati cellphone mo.
Ilang sandali ang lumipas.
Maya doesn't move.
She simply stares at her mother.
Ibigay mo.
Maya's grip tightens.
For a moment...
It looks like she's going to refuse.
Then...
Slowly...
She places her phone into Jennifer's outstretched hand.
Jennifer takes it without another word.
Silence.
Ricardo exhales heavily.
He finally stands.
Kung may oras kang magkulong sa kwarto...
Mag-scroll sa cellphone...
Kung ano pa ginagawa mo
May oras ka ring ayusin 'tong mga pagkakamali mo.
Pause.
Hindi namin palalakihin ang anak naming marunong umiwas sa responsibilidad.
Maya feels the weight of every word.
Habang nakatira ka sa bahay na 'to...
Kailangan mong panindigan ang mga desisyon mo.
At hindi namin kukunsintihin ang pagiging iresponsable.
The room falls silent once more.
Maya no longer argues.
No longer explains.
She simply stares at the empty space where her ipad had been.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:lost:2"]
The one place where she felt like herself...
Has just been taken away.
No one moves.
Jennifer stands frozen.
Maya's phone in one hand.
Her ipad in the other.
Ricardo remains beside her.
His shoulders heavy.
His expression unreadable.
Maya quietly wipes the tears from her face.
She doesn't argue.
She doesn't beg for her things back.
She doesn't say another word.
Slowly...
She turns away.
Jennifer instinctively takes a small step forward.
Almost as if she wants to call out to her.
But nothing comes out.
Maya walks toward the staircase.
Each step is slow.
Measured.
[signal arg="heartbeat:on"]
[signal arg="emotion_persist:jealous:2"]
Heavy.
Ricardo watches her in silence.
His jaw clenches.
He tells himself...
This is for her own good.
Maya climbs the stairs.
She never looks back.
The house is completely silent.
Only the sound of her footsteps echoes through the hallway.
At the top of the stairs...
She disappears behind the corner.
A moment later...
CLICK.
The sound of her bedroom door closing.
Then..
LOCK.
The small sound echoes louder than anyone expected.
Neither Jennifer nor Ricardo speaks.
Jennifer continues staring at the staircase.
Still holding Maya's belongings.
She looks down at the ipad.
Then at the phone.
She hugs them close to her chest.
As though convincing herself...
She had done the right thing.
Ricardo slowly sits back down.
He lets out a long, exhausted sigh.
...
Sana maintindihan niya balang araw.
Jennifer doesn't answer.
Her eyes never leave the second floor.
Kailangan lang niyang matauhan.
The words linger in the room.
Neither of them notices...
That the house feels quieter than ever before.
Not peaceful.
Empty.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:lost:2"]
Upstairs...
Behind the locked bedroom door...
Maya sits on the floor.
Her back against the door.
She pulls her knees close to her chest.
She stares blankly at the opposite wall.
No tears.
No anger.
Just silence.
The place that once felt like her refuge...
Now feels like a cage.
Downstairs...
Jennifer and Ricardo remain convinced they had protected their daughter from making the biggest mistake of her life.
They never realized...
That in trying so desperately to keep Maya on the path they had chosen for her...
They had pushed her further away than ever before.
The conversation had ended.
But the distance between them...
Had only just begun.
The house feels unusually quiet.
Not because no one is home.
But because no one speaks anymore.
