She turns her phone face down.
The room falls silent once more.
Days pass.
Then weeks.
The argument slowly fades into memory.
But its wounds remain.
Maya waits for the day her parents might finally understand what she tried to tell them.
Ricardo convinces himself that his daughter is simply being rebellious.
Jennifer believes that, with enough discipline, Maya will eventually come to her senses.
None of them realize...
That instead of bringing the family back together...
They are quietly drifting farther apart.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:lost:2"]
The SCHOOL BELL rings.
[signal arg="sfx:school_bell"]
Days turn into weeks.
Weeks slowly become months.
Nothing changes.
Except...
Everything does.
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
The family eats breakfast in silence.
Jennifer scrolls through her phone.
Ricardo reads through Maya's latest grade report.
He slowly places it on the table.
His expression is heavy.
Hindi ako nadidisappoint dahil bumagsak ka.
